    "(1) Suppose you bet at random on Horse #2 in a threehorse race, where all three horses at the outset are indistinguishable with respect to all of their respective racingrelevant properties.",
    "(Of course, the idea is that in MHP 3 we have a three-door \"race, \" and the bet is the initial selection of one of the three doors.)",
    "(2) From (1), we deduce that your odds of winning at t, the moment the race starts, are 1 3.",
    "(3) Suppose as well that during the race, at t ′ (t ′ > t), Horse #3 suddenly comes up lame and is out for good, while Horse #1 and Horse #2 continue running, neck and neck.",
    "(4) From (3), we deduce that your odds of winning at t ′′ (t ′′ > t ′), the moment after Horse #3 drops out, are 1 2."
